<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-14008] camel-as2 - AS2 Connection can only handle one connection (connection recovery needed)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-14008</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This bug was originally found by:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=EMBEE&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;EMBEE&quot;&gt;EMBEE&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The AS2 component creates one HTTP connection with the other party. If nothing happens for a while and the other party decides to close down the connection the component does not attempt to create a new session.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This bug was found by running the program a few hours and when a new message was to be send the connection was already closed down by the other party.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The component should create a new connection with the other party.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;OSGI with Karaf&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
